Minnesota musician John Munson shared a bit about the upcoming The New Standards Holiday Shows, and why they’re not on New Year’s Eve.

You can catch The New Standards live for their upcoming Holiday Shows at The State Theatre in Minneapolis Dec. 5 & 6.

Watch Jeff Tweedy and band perform "Out in the Dark" at The Current
Support The Current: https://support.mpr.org/youtube or hit the Thanks button

In September, Wilco frontman Jeff Tweedy released his solo triple album, "Twilight Override." Tweedy and his band visited The Current studio to play songs from the album, including "Out in the Dark," above.

Jeff Tweedy’s 2025 album, "Twilight Override," is available on dBpm Records.

Jeff Tweedy – vocals and guitar
Sammy Tweedy – vocals and keyboards / synths
Spencer Tweedy – drums
Sima Cunningham – bass and vocals

author: The Current
description:
Watch Jeff Tweedy and band perform in The Current studio
Support The Current: https://support.mpr.org/youtube or hit the Thanks button

In September, Wilco frontman Jeff Tweedy released his solo triple album, Twilight Override. To support the new album, Tweedy launched a tour with a band who are very close to his heart; specifically, his sons Spencer and Sammy, and Tweedy family’s musically talented neighbors, Sima Cunningham, Liam Kazar, and Macie Stewart. “I love everybody in this band so much,” Jeff Tweedy says, “and it really does feel like an extended part of my family, and my family life, because I've known everybody since they were little kids.”

As the tour made a stop in the Twin Cities for a show at First Avenue in Minneapolis, Tweedy and his band visited The Current studio to play songs from the album. Watch the performances above.

Songs Performed
00:00:00 Lou Reed Was My Babysitter
00:03:18 Enough
00:06:44 Out in the Dark
All songs from Jeff Tweedy’s 2025 album, Twilight
title: Jeff Tweedy plays songs from 'Twilight Override' at The Current
